<%= partial 'pre_alpha_warning' %>

1. Follow the PKS documentation for [Creating Clusters in PKS](https://docs.pivotal.io/runtimes/pks/create-cluster.html) to login with the `pks` CLI and create a cluster named `pas-for-kubernetes`.
1. Configure `kubectl` to point to the PKS cluster you created in the previous step by running the following command:

    ```
    pks get-credentials pas-for-kubernetes
    ```
    This will set the active `kubectl` context to point to the `pas-for-kubernetes` cluster.
1. Run the following commands to create the required systems namespace and service account in the pas-for-kubernetes cluster:

    ```
    kubectl create namespace pas-system
    kubectl create serviceaccount -n pas-system pas-system-service-account
    kubectl create clusterrolebinding pas-system-service-account-cluster-binding \
      --clusterrole=cluster-admin \
      --serviceaccount pas-system:pas-service-account
    ```

